    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese resist dyeing method in which patterns are applied to a fabric by folding, binding, stitching, twisting, compressing, or capping the fabric before dyeing it. These techniques date back to the 8th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
